beanies.name: Princess
beanies.description: Purple bear with white rose on chest, made to honor Princess Diana
beanies.special_notes: Indonesian PE pellet version most common ($5-20). 1st edition with space in poem and PVC pellets worth more. Despite myths, most Princess bears are worth under $20.

beanies.name: Peace
beanies.description: Tie-dye bear with peace symbol on chest
beanies.special_notes: Neon/bright 'pajama' color variations worth 2x. 99% have 4th/5th gen tags. Each tie-dye pattern is unique.

beanies.name: Valentino
beanies.description: White bear with red heart on chest
beanies.special_notes: Brown nose versions slightly more valuable. Misspelled tags (Origiinal) are rare errors worth 2-3x.

beanies.name: Legs
beanies.description: Green frog with orange belly, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. Early versions with darker green worth more. 1st gen hang tags extremely rare.

beanies.name: Squealer
beanies.description: Pink pig with curly tail, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. One of the longer-produced Original 9 members.

beanies.name: Spot
beanies.description: White dog with black spot on back, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. 'Spot without a spot' (all white, no spot) extremely rare, worth $1000+. Most have the spot.

beanies.name: Flash
beanies.description: Gray dolphin with white belly, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. Retired relatively early making older generations scarcer.

beanies.name: Splash
beanies.description: Black and white orca whale, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. One of the more popular Original 9 designs.

beanies.name: Chocolate
beanies.description: Brown moose with large antlers, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. One of the longest-produced Original 9, so more common overall.

beanies.name: Patti
beanies.description: Magenta/fuschia platypus, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. Early deep magenta versions more valuable than later raspberry color.

beanies.name: Cubbie
beanies.description: Brown bear, originally named Brownie, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. Originally named 'Brownie' - true Brownie tags extremely rare ($2000+). Name changed to Cubbie in 1994.

beanies.name: Pinchers
beanies.description: Red lobster with claws, one of the Original 9
beanies.special_notes: Original 9 member. Originally named 'Punchers' - original Punchers tags very rare ($1500+).

beanies.name: Mystic
beanies.description: White unicorn with iridescent horn and mane
beanies.special_notes: Fine yarn mane version more valuable than coarse. Brown horn version rare. Iridescent horn most common.

beanies.name: Stripes
beanies.special_notes: Dark gold 'fuzzy belly' version slightly more valuable. Light orange version most common.

beanies.name: Inch
beanies.special_notes: Yarn antennae version more valuable than felt antennae. Colors can vary significantly.

beanies.name: Lucky
beanies.special_notes: 7-spot version (printed spots) most common. 11-spot and 21-spot (glued felt spots) versions more valuable.

beanies.name: Peanut
beanies.special_notes: Royal blue version extremely rare ($3000+). Light blue version is standard and common.

beanies.name: Garcia
beanies.description: Tie-dye bear, tribute to Jerry Garcia
visual_identifiers: similar to Peace but no embroidery
beanies.special_notes: Retired early due to Jerry Garcia estate issues. No peace symbol - that's Peace bear. Shorter production run than Peace.

beanies.name: Maple
beanies.description: White bear with Canadian flag on chest
visual_identifiers: Canadian maple leaf flag on chest
beanies.special_notes: Canadian exclusive initially. 'Pride' tush tag version worth more. Special Olympics versions exist.

beanies.name: Erin
beanies.description: Green bear with white shamrock on chest
beanies.special_notes: Irish bear, very common due to large production. One of the most over-produced bears.

beanies.name: Hope
beanies.special_notes: Religious/spiritual theme. Later production so mostly 4th/5th gen tags exist.

beanies.name: Glory
beanies.description: White bear with American flag stars pattern
visual_identifiers: white fur with blue star pattern
beanies.special_notes: Patriotic bear with stars printed on fur. Part of the patriotic bear series with Spangle and Britannia.

beanies.name: Gobbles
beanies.description: Brown turkey with colorful tail feathers
beanies.special_notes: Popular Thanksgiving-themed Beanie. Very common, large production run.

beanies.name: Quackers
visual_identifiers: wings with or without wings variation
beanies.special_notes: Early 'wingless' version more valuable ($500+). With wings version is standard.

beanies.name: Zip
beanies.special_notes: All black version more valuable. White face version is more common. White paws variation exists.

beanies.name: Bongo
beanies.special_notes: Originally named 'Nana' - Nana tags very rare ($3000+). Tan tail version worth more than brown tail.

beanies.name: Derby
beanies.description: Brown horse with yarn or fine mane
beanies.special_notes: Coarse yarn mane version more valuable than fine mane. Star on forehead variation exists on later versions.

beanies.name: Twigs
beanies.special_notes: Spot pattern varies. Earlier retirement makes this slightly less common than some.

beanies.name: Curly
beanies.description: Brown bear with curly napped fur
beanies.special_notes: Unique curly textured fur. Very common, long production run. Errors with extra or missing features exist.

beanies.name: Ty 2K
beanies.description: White bear with 2000 confetti pattern celebrating Y2K
beanies.special_notes: Millennium commemorative bear. Mass produced for Y2K, extremely common. Almost all have 5th gen tags.

beanies.name: Bones
beanies.description: Brown hound dog with long floppy ears
beanies.special_notes: Popular dog Beanie. Early versions with darker brown fur slightly more valuable.

beanies.name: Rover
beanies.special_notes: Solid red colored dog. Less common than some other dog Beanies.

beanies.name: Wrinkles
beanies.special_notes: Bulldog with distinctive wrinkled face. Popular dog design.

beanies.name: Scottie
beanies.special_notes: Classic Scottish terrier design. All black coloring.

beanies.name: Bernie
beanies.description: Brown and white St. Bernard dog
beanies.special_notes: St. Bernard design. Brown and white coloring.

beanies.name: Doby
beanies.special_notes: Doberman design with classic black and tan markings.

beanies.name: Tracker
beanies.special_notes: Basset hound with long ears. Later production, mostly 4th/5th gen tags.

beanies.name: Spunky
beanies.special_notes: Cocker spaniel with fluffy tan fur. Later production.

beanies.name: Tuffy
beanies.special_notes: Terrier with scruffy fur texture.

beanies.name: Weenie
beanies.special_notes: Dachshund (wiener dog) with characteristic long body.

beanies.name: Snip
beanies.special_notes: Siamese cat coloring. Popular cat design.

beanies.name: Nip
beanies.description: Gold cat with white face and belly
beanies.special_notes: All gold version without white is rarer. White face version most common.

beanies.name: Pounce
beanies.special_notes: Brown tabby cat. Later production, common.

beanies.name: Ringo
beanies.special_notes: Raccoon with distinctive mask and ringed tail.

beanies.name: Stinky
beanies.special_notes: Classic black and white skunk design.

beanies.name: Sly
beanies.special_notes: Brown belly version rarer than white belly. White belly most common.

beanies.name: Nuts
beanies.special_notes: Squirrel with bushy tail. Common later production.

beanies.name: Hoot
beanies.special_notes: Brown owl design. Earlier retirement makes it slightly less common.

beanies.name: Kiwi
beanies.special_notes: Colorful toucan with distinctive large beak.

beanies.name: Scoop
beanies.description: Blue pelican with large beak pouch
beanies.special_notes: Blue pelican with distinctive beak pouch.

beanies.name: Blackie
beanies.description: Black bear, one of the early classic bears
beanies.special_notes: Classic early bear. One of the more common early bears but still valuable with 1st/2nd gen tags.

beanies.name: Teddy Brown
beanies.description: Brown teddy bear with old face or new face design
visual_identifiers: old face (pointed snout) or new face (rounder)
beanies.special_notes: Old face version (pointed snout) more valuable than new face. Part of the original Teddy series.

beanies.name: Teddy Cranberry
visual_identifiers: old face or new face design
beanies.special_notes: Early retirement makes this more valuable. Old face version worth more.

beanies.name: Teddy Jade
visual_identifiers: old face or new face design
beanies.special_notes: Early retirement makes this more valuable. Old face version worth more.

beanies.name: Teddy Magenta
visual_identifiers: old face or new face design
beanies.special_notes: Early retirement makes this more valuable. Old face version worth more.

beanies.name: Teddy Teal
visual_identifiers: old face or new face design
beanies.special_notes: Early retirement makes this more valuable. Old face version worth more.

beanies.name: Teddy Violet
visual_identifiers: old face or new face design
beanies.special_notes: Early retirement makes this more valuable. Old face version worth more.

beanies.name: Chilly
beanies.special_notes: Very early retirement makes this one of the more valuable bears. Don't confuse with later polar bears.

beanies.name: Peking
beanies.description: Panda bear with black and white coloring
beanies.special_notes: Early retirement makes this valuable. Classic panda design.

beanies.name: Valentina
beanies.description: Fuchsia/magenta bear with white heart on chest
beanies.special_notes: Female counterpart to Valentino. Later production, mostly 5th gen tags.

beanies.name: Millennium
beanies.description: Purple bear with gold MILLENNIUM embroidery
beanies.special_notes: Mass produced for Y2K, extremely common. Misspelled 'Millenium' tags worth slightly more.

beanies.name: The End
beanies.description: Black bear with THE END embroidery
beanies.special_notes: Final bear of the original Beanie Baby era. Mass produced, common.

beanies.name: Halo
beanies.description: White angel bear with wings and halo
beanies.special_notes: Brown nose version slightly rarer. Wings can be iridescent or plain.

beanies.name: Spangle
beanies.description: Patriotic American flag bear with stars and stripes
beanies.special_notes: Pink face version exists. Part of patriotic bear series.

beanies.name: Britannia
beanies.description: Brown bear with UK flag on chest
beanies.special_notes: UK exclusive initially. One of the more valuable country bears.

beanies.name: Fortune
beanies.description: Panda bear celebrating Chinese New Year
beanies.special_notes: Panda for Chinese New Year. More common than original Peking panda.

beanies.name: Fuzz
beanies.description: Brown bear with extra fuzzy fur texture
beanies.special_notes: Unique fuzzy texture. Later production, mostly 5th gen tags.

beanies.name: Groovy
beanies.special_notes: Brighter colors than Peace bear. Each pattern unique.

beanies.name: Libearty

beanies.name: Osito

beanies.special_notes: Mexican flag bear. Part of the country bear series.

beanies.name: Germania
beanies.special_notes: German flag bear. European exclusive initially.

beanies.special_notes: Tan version without mouth more valuable. Pink version most common.

beanies.special_notes: Classic goldfish design. Early production more valuable.

beanies.name: Crunch
